Date:  0/0/1978
Source:  Gold Mining at Waihi (Glossary)
Author:  McARA
Vol / Page:  324
Edition:
Quote:  Head sample: A sample of the ore taken as it entered the plant in order to determine its average value. A tail sample was taken as the tailings were discharged, so that the percentage and quantity of the precious metals being recovered were always known.
